    "difficulty": "medium",
    "sourceYear": 2024,
    "en": {
      "question": "A and B can do a work in 18 days. B and C in 24 days. A and C in 36 days. How long will A alone take?",
      "options": [
        "28 days",
        "30 days",
        "36 days",
        "48 days"
      ],
      "explanation": "2(A+B+C) = 1/18 + 1/24 + 1/36 = 4/72 + 3/72 + 2/72 = 9/72 = 1/8. A+B+C = 1/16. A alone = (A+B+C) - (B+C) = 1/16 - 1/24 = 3/48 - 2/48 = 1/48. A alone = 48 days."
    },
    "hi": {
